# ar2832package1

<!-- badges: start -->

<!-- badges: end -->

The goal of ar2832package1 is to provide functionality for my package.
These functions are for use only with Arnau Rovira and no other people

## Installation

You can install the released version of ar2832package1 from
[CRAN](https://CRAN.R-project.org) with:

``` r
install.packages("ar2832package1")
```

## Example: usage of the different functions of the package

This is a basic example which shows you how to solve a common problem:

``` r
library(ar2832package1)
## basic example code


if(!file.exists("zip.test.gz")){
  download.file(
    "https://web.stanford.edu/~hastie/ElemStatLearn/datasets/zip.test.gz",
    "zip.test.gz")
}

#Prepare the data:
zip.test.gz <- data.table::fread("zip.test.gz")
label.col.i <- which(names(zip.test.gz)=="V1")
label.col.name <- "V1"
X.mat <- as.matrix(zip.test.gz[, -..label.col.i])
K <- 5
#KMEANS FUNCTION
res <- KMEANS(X.mat, K=5)
res$clusters[5]
```
